A '''headset comlink''' or '''comlink headset''' was a communications device worn as headgear, often by [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]]. It was used to communicate between ships and cruisers.

[[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] pilots of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] wore headset [[Comlink/Legends|comlinks]] when the [[Delta-7 Aethersprite-class light interceptor/Legends|Delta-7 ''Aethersprite''-class light interceptor]] was introduced, and continued to do so with the introduction of the [[Eta-2 Actis-class interceptor/Legends|Eta-2 ''Actis''-class interceptor]]. Members of the [[Bothan police force]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kothlis/Legends|Kothlis]] utilized such devices.

Jedi of the [[New Jedi Order]] wore similar devices; [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]], and [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] were known to have used identical headsets during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]], and [[Shado Vao]] sported a smaller version during the [[Massacre at Ossus]], while piloting a [[J-1 shuttle]] from [[Ossus/Legends|Ossus]].

